Pre-requisites:
  - make sure to run on python3.7.1
  - make sure that tk_tcl is in python_build (see https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/issues/1375)

Getting the car up and running
1) run LanScan to get IP of Adeept PiCar

2) login to Adeept PiCar via pi@[IP Address]

3) use the password you hopefully stored in your keychain

3) check if server.py is running

3a) if not execute /home/pi/startup.sh

On Client side

 1) go to Adeept_PiCar-B repo clone
 2) go to folder /Client
 3) run "python client.py"
